'''Hifumi Shimoyama''', born 1930 in Japan, is a composer of contemporary [[concert music]]. Since the 1960s, Shimoyama's music has been regularly featured on [[World Music Days]] festivals across Europe and Asia, and sponsored by the [[International Society for Contemporary Music]] (ISCM). Shimoyama is the founder of GROUP 20.5, the internationally recognized group of Japanese [[avant garde]] composers.

